      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "jdbc:sqlserver://[^\\s;\"']+(?:;|\\?)[^\\s\"']*(?:password|PASSWORD|pwd|PWD)\\s*=\\s*(?!\\{|\\$\\{|<)([A-Za-z0-9!@#$%^&*()_+=\\[\\]|:,.<>?/\\\\~-]{8,50})(?![}>;])",
        "message": "SQL Server JDBC connection string with embedded password detected - CRITICAL. JDBC URLs with password parameters (jdbc:sqlserver://host:port;password=xxx or jdbc:sqlserver://host;database=db;password=xxx) expose SQL Server database credentials in Java/.NET application code or configuration files. This grants full database access including read, write, administrative operations, stored procedure execution, and potentially server-level access if using privileged accounts like SA. IMMEDIATE ACTIONS: 1) Remove password parameter from JDBC URL immediately, 2) Rotate compromised SQL Server credentials using ALTER LOGIN, 3) Use secure credential management: Windows Authentication (Integrated Security=True), Azure Active Directory authentication for Azure SQL, Kerberos authentication, connection pooling with secure credential providers, or encrypted configuration files, 4) Review SQL Server error logs and audit trails for suspicious activity, 5) Implement connection encryption with SSL/TLS, 6) Use principle of least privilege for database accounts, 7) Enable SQL Server auditing for login events.",
